OL,3,CAlmost #11 billion per year 'could be
OL,4,Cfreed up if people quit smoking'
OL,6,FAlmost #11 billion per year could be
OL,7,Ffreed up and spent in England's
OL,8,Fcommunities if people quit smoking,
OL,9,Faccording to new research.
OL,11,FThe study, from experts at the
OL,12,FUniversity of Sheffield, found poorer
OL,13,Fregions of the country could get the
OL,14,Fmost benefit from money saved on
OL,15,Ftobacco.
