OL,3,CAlmost #11 billion per year 'could be
OL,4,Cfreed up if people quit smoking'
OL,6,FA team from the university's
OL,7,Faddictions research group looked at
OL,8,Fhow much people spend on cigarettes
OL,9,Fand tobacco each year and how this
OL,10,Fmoney could be spent instead in towns,
OL,11,Fcities and villages.
OL,13,FThey found that #10.9 billion ` made
OL,14,Fup of spending on tobacco minus the
OL,15,Famount kept by local retailers as
OL,16,Fprofit (7%) ` could be reinvested in
OL,17,Flocal shops, services and on
OL,18,Fentertainment.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/9
