OL,3,CAlmost #11 billion per year 'could be
OL,4,Cfreed up if people quit smoking'
OL,6,FStudy author Dr Damon Morris said the
OL,7,Fmoney currently leaving local
OL,8,Fcommunities is taken by the tobacco
OL,9,Findustry as profit or by the
OL,10,FGovernment in tax.
OL,12,F"This is money that people can instead
OL,13,Fspend on other things such as in
OL,14,Fshops, on entertainment or other
OL,15,Fservices," he said.
OL,17,FHe added: "The total economic benefit
OL,18,Fof going completely smoke-free would
OL,19,Fbe greater than #10.9 billion.
