OL,3,CAlmost #11 billion per year 'could be
OL,4,Cfreed up if people quit smoking'
OL,6,F"As well as the local area benefits,
OL,7,Fthere would be savings made by the NHS
OL,8,Fwith fewer ill smokers, and benefits
OL,9,Fto the wider economy through fewer
OL,10,Fpeople being unable to work due to
OL,11,Fsmoking-related illness."
OL,13,FIt comes after the Tobacco and Vapes
OL,14,FBill was introduced to Parliament,
OL,15,Fwhich will restrict the sale of
OL,16,Ftobacco so that anyone turning 15 this
OL,17,Fyear, or younger, will never legally
OL,18,Fbe sold cigarettes.
